===Etymology===
Origin: 1585–95; in {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|silex||hard stone, flint}}. Subsequently, {{m|en|silicon}} was identified by the chemist [[w:Antoine Lavoisier|Antoine Lavoisier]] in 1787 as a component element of the {{m|la||silex}}<ref>{{R:Dictionary.com|silex}}</ref> or {{m|la||silicis}}. Compare {{m|en|silicate}}.

